article.headline: Howard 82, Norfolk St. 77
article.story: NORFOLK, Va. -- Calvin Thompson scored 24 points and Dadrian Collins had 21, leading Howard to an 82-77 win over Norfolk State on Monday night. Curtis White added 18 points and Kandi Mukole had 11 for the Bison (5-14, 4-1 Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference), who have won three straight and four of five. The Bison opened the season with 13 losses in their first 14 games. Collins also grabbed a team-high eight rebounds and nailed four 3-pointers for the Bison, who were 11-for-24 from beyond the arc (45.8 percent). The Spartans finished just 5-for-16 from long range (31.3 percent). Michael Deloach scored 22 points and Rob Hampton had 21 for the Spartans (3-13, 2-3), who had their first two-game winning streak of the season snapped. The Spartans lost despite outscoring Howard 40-18 in the paint and 8-0 on the fastbreak.
